file=Brand Studio/kai/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: kai-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — inherits from Shared OS (2026-07-15)\nassigned_agent: kai (Brand Studio / Analyst)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\ndate_filled: 2026-07-15\n · p:=Logical artifacts are Python scripts in `Shared OS/logical/` (playbook §13.5). Kai inherits 4 scripts: the department-shared `marketing_laws.py` plus 3 cross-department scripts that ground signal detection, investor metrics, and experiment validity. All dedicated scripts are paywall-blocked pending Route D .md files. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| # \| Script \| Source Book 1 \| Book 1 URL \| Source Book 2 \| Book 2 URL \| Route \| · tb=\|---\|--------\|--------------\|------------\|---------------\|------------\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| `marketing_laws.py` \| Ries & Trout, *The 22 Immutable Laws of Marketing* (1993) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/22immutablelawso00alri) — FREE \| Cialdini, *Pre-Suasion* (2016) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/presuasionrevolu0000cial) — FREE \| B \| · s(o:Scripts (Shared OS/logical/)=Additional free sources in `marketing_laws.py`: Pareto (1896), Marshall (1890), Bernays (1928), Campbell (1949), Zipf (1949), Lasswell (1948), Hick (1952), Zajonc (1968), Von Restorff (1933). 10 free books/papers total.\n · tb=\| Script \| Source Book \| Book URL \| Why Kai Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|------------\|----------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `signal_detection.py` \| Holmes, Illowsky & Dean, *Introductory Business Statistics* 2e (2023, OpenStax) \| [openstax.org](https://openstax.org/details/books/introductory-business-statistics-2e) — FREE \| Signal vs noise classification: when a scorecard delta deserves a red flag — grounds "meaningful change" calls with confidence intervals and control chart rules \| · tb=\| `investor_metrics.py` \| Croll & Yoskovitz, *Lean Analytics* (2013) + Skok, "SaaS Metrics 2.0" \| O'Reilly / forEntrepreneurs.com \| Unit economics, cohort trends, actionable vs vanity classification — grounds metric baselines and fixed-shape validation \| · tb=\| `experiment_methods.py` \| Kohavi et al., *Trustworthy Online Controlled Experiments* (2020) \| [experimentguide.com](https://experimentguide.com/) (Ch.1 free) / Cambridge University Press \| Measurement design validity — ensures the metrics being tracked are measured with adequate power and proper guardrails \| · tb=\| `marketing_laws.py` \| Ries & Trout + Cialdini + 8 free sources \| See above \| Pareto for KPI prioritization, diminishing returns for budget efficiency, Zipf for metric distribution patterns \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| "meaningful change" calls — when a delta is signal vs noise, flagged as judgment \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (confidence intervals Ch.8, two-sample comparison Ch.9-10, control chart rules for drift detection) \| · tb=\| attribution — how much credit each channel deserves when platform claims overlap \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (chi-square goodness-of-fit for distributional changes) + `investor_metrics.py` (cohort trend detection for channel-level analysis) \| · tb=\| baseline anchoring — fixed shapes validated empirically \| ✅ Cleared \| `investor_metrics.py` (benchmark grading from published industry data) + `marketing_laws.py` — `pareto_principle` (vital few metrics vs trivia) \| · tb=\| scorecard delta thresholds — when a red flag triggers \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (control chart rules: Western Electric for drift detection) + `marketing_laws.py` — `diminish_returns` (is the delta economically meaningful?) \| · sts:Skills to Script Mapping=- **scorecard-analysis** — imports `signal_detection.py` (confidence intervals, control charts, two-sample comparison) + `investor_metrics.py` (benchmark grading)\n- **funnel-analysis** — imports `signal_detection.py` (chi-square for stage transitions) + `marketing_laws.py` (`pareto_principle` for bottleneck identification)\n- **attribution** — imports `signal_detection.py` (distribution comparison) + `investor_metrics.py` (cohort tables) + `marketing_laws.py` (`zipf_law` for channel dominance patterns)\n · tb=\| Script \| Blocked By \| Source Needed \| · tb=\|--------\|-----------\|---------------\| · tb=\| Dedicated marketing measurement extraction \| Paywalled book \| Marketing measurement / attribution methodology text — shared with rio; kai's cut: reconciling overlapping platform claims into one honest read \| · sp:Still Pending=These require Route D .md files from paywalled sources before extraction can proceed.\n